Boris Johnson swerved questions about his feelings following the Tory revolt that put an end to his leadership last week. The Prime Minister was asked whether he felt "betrayed" after Sajid Javid and Rishi Sunak sparked an exodus of ministers, PPSs, and envoys that led to his fall from grace. Mr Johnson bypassed questions about his emotional state as he insisted his job is to "continue to deliver" the Tory manifesto until a successor is selected. MORE TO FOLLOW...